+Let me rewrite the `findSwappedWires` function with a cleaner approach:Implementation complete. 
+
+**Summary:**
+
+- **`simulate(gates, inputs)`**: Processes gates in dependency order using a worklist algorithm. Each gate fires when both inputs have values, computing AND/OR/XOR operations.
+
+- **`findSwappedWires(gates)`**: Uses structural analysis of the binary adder pattern to identify swapped wires:
+  1. z00 must be XOR(x00, y00)
+  2. zNN (N>0) must be XOR with input from XOR(xNN, yNN)
+  3. z(max+1) must be OR gate
+  4. XOR(xNN, yNN) for N>0 must not output z wires
+  5. AND(xNN, yNN) must not output z wires
+  6. Checks that partial sum and generate wires are used correctly by downstream gates
+
+The algorithm runs in O(gates²) time, handling 220+ gates in under 5 seconds. Tests verify correctness on various swap patterns including single swaps, multiple swaps, and performance on 45-bit circuits.
